<h1><i class="fa fa-lock"></i>Managing Privacy</h1>

<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#help"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>Help</a></li>
	<li><a href="#help/sharing-news"><i class="fa fa-newspaper"></i>Sharing News</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-lock"></i>Managing Privacy</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p><%= application.name %> gives you easy to use privacy controls which enable you to decide which news posts you want to share with everyone and which posts you want to keep to your friends. </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-lock"></i>Privacy Controls</h2>
			<p>When you create a new post, to the lower right side of the new post panel, you will see a set of radio buttons which are your privacy controls. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/sharing-news/managing-privacy/new-private-post.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Privacy Controls"><img src="images/help/sharing-news/managing-privacy/new-private-post.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Privacy Controls</div>
			</div>

			<p>The privacy controls allow you to choose between two settings: </p>
			<ul>
				<li><label>Connections</label> - this post is visible only to your friends.</li>
				<li><label>Public</label> - this post is visible to anyone only your public news page.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-globe"></i>Your Public News Page</h2>
			<p>To view your Public News Page, go to your <a href="#help/creating-profile/viewing-home-page">Public Home Page</a> and then click on the "News" tab. If you have not marked any of your posts as publicly visible, then you will see "No posts."</p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/sharing-news/managing-privacy/public-news-page.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="A Public News Page"><img src="images/help/sharing-news/managing-privacy/public-news-page.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">A Public News Page</div>
			</div>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-snowflake"></i>Your Privacy Preferences</h2>
			<p>By default, each post will be visible only to your friends.  However, let's say that you're an extrovert and would like your posts to default to "public" instead.  You can do so using your privacy preferences.  To view your privacy preferences, go to the View menu in the <a href="#apps/topic-viewer">News Browser</a> app and click on "Preferences". </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="dropdown menu" src="images/help/sharing-news/managing-privacy/preferences-menu-item@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">"Preferences" on the View Menu</div>
			</div>

			<p>This will bring up the preferences dialog where you can set your preferred Default Privacy. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/sharing-news/managing-privacy/preferences-dialog.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Preferences Dialog"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/sharing-news/managing-privacy/preferences-dialog.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Preferences Dialog</div>
			</div>
	</ol>
</div>